7. Logging & output (this is the payoff)

Write a runs/<timestamp>/ folder containing:


round_<t>.json — pass rates, evidence bundle, every candidate with accept/reject + deltas.
harness_<t>.json — snapshot of the harness after each round.
summary.md — a table of held-in / held-out pass rate per round, and a human-readable list of which edits were accepted and why.


The most interesting artifact is what edits the model proposed about its own failures — make these easy to read in summary.md.


8. Acceptance criteria (definition of done)


python loop.py runs end-to-end on the bundled coding suite with only ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set.
Held-in and held-out pass rates are reported per round.
At least one round shows an accepted edit with non-negative deltas on both splits.
summary.md clearly shows the harness growing (blocks gaining targeted instructions) across rounds.
Rejected edits are logged with their deltas so the gate is auditable.



9. Build order for Claude Code


Scaffold repo + config, write 20 coding tasks with tests.
model.py (verify a single call works).
evaluate.py + sandbox runner (verify pass-rate on h0).
mine.py → propose.py (inspect the proposed edits by hand first).
validate.py + merge.py.
loop.py + logging + summary.md.
Run T=3 cheap end-to-end, read the logs, then scale T/task count.



10. Gotchas (read before running a big job)


Cost / quota: the loop fans out to many model calls. Programmatic API usage draws from your API credits (separate from a chat subscription) — start with T=2, K=2, and a small suite, then scale.
Noisy deltas: with too few tasks, one flip swings the pass rate and the gate promotes junk. Use enough tasks per split (≥10 each) so a 1-task change isn't decisive.
Sandbox safety: run model-generated code in a locked-down subprocess (timeout, no network, restricted builtins). Never exec it in-process.
Editable surface: keep harness blocks explicit and labeled, or proposals come out vague and unmergeable.
Determinism: seed the split and set temperature low for the solver role so deltas reflect harness changes, not sampling noise. The proposer role can run warmer for edit diversity.